#Approach:

Remove Outermost Parentheses – Depth / Count Approach

Is problem me hume har primitive valid parentheses string ke outermost brackets remove karne hote hain.

Hum ek count variable rakhte hain jo current depth batata hai
ki hum kitne nested parentheses ke andar hain.

String ko left se right traverse karte hain.

Agar current character '(' ho:
to pehle check karte hain ki count 0 hai ya nahi.
Agar count 0 nahi hai, matlab ye outermost opening bracket nahi hai,
to ise answer me add kar dete hain.
Uske baad count increase kar dete hain.

Agar current character ')' ho:
to pehle count decrease karte hain
kyunki ek level close ho raha hai.
Phir check karte hain ki count 0 hai ya nahi.
Agar count 0 nahi hai, matlab ye outermost closing bracket nahi hai,
to ise answer me add kar dete hain.

Is tarah har primitive string ke sirf outermost opening aur closing bracket skip ho jate hain
aur baaki saare brackets answer me add ho jate hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public String removeOuterParentheses(String s) {

        int count = 0;
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();

        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++){
            char ch = s.charAt(i);
            if(ch == '('){
                if(count != 0){
                    sb.append(ch);
                }
                count++;
            }
            if(ch == ')'){
                count--;
                if(count != 0){
                    sb.append(ch);
                }
            }
        }
        return sb.toString();
        
    }
}
